laboratory_examinations.findings: Positive for trisomy 21 with a risk of 1/6 and for trisomy 18 with a risk of 1/24; fetal NT measured 6.44 mm, PAPP-A was 0.53 MOM, HCG was 0.70 MOM.
Normal chromosome analysis and normal microarray results, specifically negative for Noonan's syndrome.

Early onset growth restriction with the fetus measuring 18 weeks; multiple anomalies including shortened long bones, clenched fists, bilateral clubfeet with high suspicion of polydactyly, cerebellar hypoplasia, abnormal calvarium, micrognathia, low-set ears, single umbilical artery, and possible ventral septal defect (VSD).
Positive for heterozygous NIPBL pathogenic variant c.1713 1716delACAA; this variant was not found in parental DNA and therefore likely de novo; however, gonadal mosaicism cannot be excluded.
